<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                        <head>273. Telegram 852 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d273fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/10–555. Official
                                Use Only. Drafted by Nagoski.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-10-07">October 7, 1955, 8:34
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d273-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d273-1"/>
                        <p>852. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Your 819, para 13, cites 19 still in jail. Your despatch No. 1 of August
                            3 lists 25 in jail. Seven of these since released, making balance still
                            in jail 18. Comment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>